      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_12",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A-3 Note that the series on the left is simply xexp(−x2/2). By integration by parts,",
        "bbox": [
          0.5223529411764706,
          0.16424242424242425,
          0.9184313725490196,
          0.19454545454545455
        ],
        "order": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_2",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A–1 The centroid G of the triangle is collinear with H and O (Euler line), and the centroid lies two-thirds of the way from A to M. Therefore H is also two-thirds of the way from A to F, so AF = 15. Since the triangles BF H and AFC are similar (they're right triangles and",
        "bbox": [
          0.09333333333333334,
          0.16484848484848486,
          0.49019607843137253,
          0.2381818181818182
        ],
        "order": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_13",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "and so by induction,",
        "bbox": [
          0.5568627450980392,
          0.24484848484848484,
          0.691764705882353,
          0.2593939393939394
        ],
        "order": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_3",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "we have",
        "bbox": [
          0.12784313725490196,
          0.2781818181818182,
          0.18352941176470589,
          0.2909090909090909
        ],
        "order": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_14",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Thus the desired integral is simply",
        "bbox": [
          0.5576470588235294,
          0.3096969696969697,
          0.7850980392156863,
          0.3242424242424242
        ],
        "order": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_4",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "or",
        "bbox": [
          0.12705882352941175,
          0.3339393939393939,
          0.14352941176470588,
          0.34484848484848485
        ],
        "order": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_5",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Now but",
        "bbox": [
