        "text": "",
        "bbox": [
          0.5576470588235294,
          0.5933333333333334,
          0.7780392156862745,
          0.6103030303030303
        ],
        "order": 16
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_19",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A-5 We may discard any solutions for which a1 ≠ a2, since those come in pairs; so assume a1 = a2. Similarly, we may assume that a3 = a4, a5 = a6, a7 = a8, a9 = a10. Thus we get the equation",
        "bbox": [
          0.5231372549019608,
          0.6181818181818182,
          0.9192156862745098,
          0.676969696969697
        ],
        "order": 17
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0009",
    "kind": "text_cluster_panel",
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001",
    "primary_id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_9",
    "source": "text_cluster",
    "member_count": 2,
    "elements": [
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_9",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "– Except for the player to move, each player has k pennies; – The player to move has at least k pennies.",
        "bbox": [
          0.14666666666666667,
          0.649090909090909,
          0.49019607843137253,
          0.6987878787878787
        ],
        "order": 18
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_10",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "We claim then that the game terminates if and only if the number of players is a power of 2. First suppose the number of players is even; then after m complete rounds, every other player, starting with the player who moved first, will have m more pennies than initially, and the others will all have 0. Thus we are reduced to the situation with half as many players; by this process, we eventually reduce to the case where the number of play- ers is odd. However, if there is more than one player, after two complete rounds everyone has as many pen- nies as they did before (here we need m ≥ 2), so the game fails to terminate. This verifies the claim.",
        "bbox": [
          0.12705882352941175,
          0.7078787878787879,
          0.49019607843137253,
          0.8818181818181818
        ],
        "order": 19
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0010",
    "kind": "text_cluster_panel",
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001",
    "primary_id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_20",
    "source": "text_cluster",
    "member_count": 2,
    "elements": [
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_20",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Again, we may assume a1 = a3 and a5 = a7, so we get 4/a1 + 4/a5 + 2/a9 = 1; and a1 = a5, so 8/a1 +2/a9 = 1. This implies that (a1 − 8)(a9 − 2) = 16, which by counting has 5 solutions. Thus N1o is odd.",
        "bbox": [
          0.556078431372549,
          0.7169696969696969,
          0.92,
          0.7745454545454545
        ],
        "order": 20
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_21",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A–6 Clearly xn+1 is a polynomial in c of degree n, so it suf- fi ces to identify n values of c for which xn+1 = 0. We claim these are c = n − 1 − 2r for r = 0, 1, . . .,n − 1; in this case, xk is the coefficient of −1 in the polyno- mial f (t) = (1 − t)(1 + t)n−1−r. This can be verified by noticing that f satisfi es the differential equation",
        "bbox": [
          0.5231372549019608,
          0.7836363636363637,
          0.92,
          0.8715151515151515
        ],
        "order": 21
      }
    ]
  },
  {
